==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mainpernable
<hw>Main"per*na*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>main</ets> hand + <ets>pernable</ets>, for <ets>prenable</ets>,
that may be taken, pregnable. See <er>Mainpernor</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Capable of being admitted to give surety by
mainpernors; able to be mainprised.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mainpernor</ent>⟦br⟧
